When you come to a dealership, make sure you've  done your research on the car you really want. Visit truecar.com and see what the average customer pays for that car, print it and see what dealership will match it. Don't try to get a discount on that "truecar" price because you might not get it, then you will be mad at the dealership because they can't go in the hole for you to buy the car. Find a sales rep that will treat you right and is knowledgeable about the product, then buy from them.

朋友，你好！作为餐厅服务人员，我想我们应该说明一下，谢谢。首先，我很清楚的记得，您和您的朋友是坐在我们店里的靠窗户的第一张桌子。您和朋友一起点了5个菜，并且每个菜都吃得非常干净，在用餐的过程，我们也不只一次的问了您"味道可以吗？""需要加米饭吗？" 您和朋友都说"挺好的"。（如果当时对我们的菜品有任何不满意的地方，可以提出来，我们会立刻重新做，达到您的满意。）现在您说那些都是...请问那么您吃的是什么呢......谢谢。还有，你说出来"要小费"：当时找给您零钱之后，您并没有留下 小费在桌子上，而您并没有任何对我们服务不满意的地方。所以我们才会问您要小费。如果有任何对我们服务，菜品，不满意的地方可以直言不讳的和我们讲，我们会尽最大能力做得更好。最后，请你记得在国外，给小费是一种习俗，一种美德，一种礼仪。请您出去了，谨记，不要再给咱们华人丢了脸。谢谢。希望下次再来，有任何不满意的地方可以直接告诉我们。谢谢。

We took our 4 yr old boxer to see the vet in township in nc. He has a growth on his eyelid. It popped up suddenly and has grown and a tremendous rate. They looked him over and gave us a estimate for $2500. To have the mass removed and reconstruct his eyelid. Plus they freaked us out saying it was cancer. Of course thus us way out if our budget. We then went to another vet and they looked at it took some cells and looked under the microscope and no cancer just a hystiocytoma. Google it.

Boxers are prone to get these. Something a vet should know right away. Needless to say it cost only $200. To have this done. How can a company that treats animals want to rip off family's? They made us feel awful cuz we couldn't afford the $2500. Please do not take ur pet here. Only in it for money and want to RIP u off.
They have been bought out, the prices have soared, the communication about your pet declined. Sadly, a great place gone bad. I go to Long's now. The care and the cost are wonderful!

It should be expected that CVS is expensive.. they are a specialized surgery and emergency facility. For surgery, you're using a doctor who performs a specialized surgery several times a week vs your primary vet who maybe does it a few times a year.  Get dog health insurance (healthy paws). In just 4 years, I've received reimbursement checks worth 92+ months of my health insurance payment.
